 ABUJA – Rotarian Hajia Zainab Omowunmi Owonikoko, the Rotary Club of Abuja Garki Neighborhood’s first female president, has presented its sustainable initiatives and activities for the year 2022–2023 with the aim of boosting local and world­wide impact. She stated in her speech at the official flag-off of the Rotary year 2022–2023 on Fri­day in Abuja that the Club’s priorities typically revolve around fostering peace, battling disease, providing clean water, saving mothers and children, assisting with education, boosting local economies, and preserving the environment. Owonikoko, who will oversee Club operations in District 9125 Nigeria for the foreseeable future, stated that family health outreach programs form part of the Club’s annual projects. Others are com­petition for a career lecture and quiz competition for schools in FCT, organising Polio /Covid-19 seminars, rallies, road shows as well as sponsorship of 20 youths to Rotary Youth Leadership Academy (RYLA). She added that the club will also focus on: “Water & sanitation project (A joint project with our sponsored interact Club), tree planting/ environmental sanitation in our sponsor schools in FCT, economic & community de­velopment projects (women empowerment, donation of sewing machine, donation of grinding machine). “Donation of Wheel Chairs to School of the Blind, donation of exercise books and school, donation of Laboratory equipment to our sponsored schools, donation of Medical Equip­ment to Health Center in our adopted Village, 1 year full scholarship to 30 indi­gent students and donation of Computers and Accesso­ries to our sponsored school in FCT.” Owonikoko, having emerged as the first female Club President officially as­sumed office on Friday, July 1st, to pilot the affairs of the Club and work towards the actualisation of Rotary goals and ideal of service during the year.